# JavaScript Linter Rule

This rule configures ESLint for JavaScript and Svelte files in the frontend source directory.

## Purpose

- Identifies potential errors and problematic patterns
- Enforces best practices for JavaScript code
- Ensures code quality and consistency

## Configuration

```json
{
  "language": "javascript",
  "patterns": [
    {
      "files": ["frontend/src/**/*.js", "frontend/src/**/*.svelte"],
      "rules": {
        "linters": {
          "enabled": true,
          "eslint": {
            "enabled": true
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

## Usage Notes

- ESLint provides real-time feedback about code issues
- Marks potential problems directly in the editor
- Can be configured to auto-fix certain types of issues
- Works alongside Prettier for complete code quality control 